Available for deployment!

Despite everything our dedicated team of tiny engineeres continues to push forward in the field of tiny military transportation. Our latest offering is the fresh addition of two self-propelled artillery systems. These fully enclosed machines are perfect for any army - whether you desire to lob shells from afar or blast enemy strogpoints at point blank range.

This kit includes all the necessary parts you need to add either long ranged SPG or a powerful Assault Cannon to your force. Included a host of optional accessories.

This vehicle is perfect for any games involving tiny tanks or robots in 6 to 8mm scale.

Available for deployment!

Even if some deride it for it's seeming lack of firepower, heavy mortar carrier forms a vital part of many an imperial army. Quick and accurate it can launch prompt and precise bombardments in close cooperation with frontline troops. 

The same chassis is also utilized for a family of recon and command vehicles. These open-topped vehicles make great use of chassis' powerful engines to perform reconnaissance and patrol tasks.

These stls allow you to add heavy mortar carrier, recon tank or a command vehicle to your tiny (around 8mm) grimdark forces. Unlike previous releases this one designed for a track units (along with some hull details) to be printed as separate parts to improve printing and allow for addition of more variants down the line. So far some variants are included with track guards and variants of vehicle hulls. Recon and command tanks can be printed with their interior covered with tarp if you are not feeling like painting the interiors. Command tank includes both heavy flamethrower and heavy gyrojet as it's main weapons. In addition a mine clearing device and two variants of sideskirt armour are included for further customization. I also plan on adding some more cosmetic variants and accessories for these in the future. 

Finally, apologies for a long wait, hopefully I can pick up pace going forwards.

UPDATE 11.04.2024 - fixed undersides of the trackunits to sit flat added a dozer blade to accessories

UPDATE 05.11.2024 - fixed an issue with tracks that failed to adhere to the the trackunit under some circumstances as pointed out to me.

UPDATE 15.03.2025 - reworked track units in preparation for the new releases on this chassis to hopefully solve the issues for good. Added a new version with quarter track guards + versions without decorations on hatch for those pesky renegades while I was at it

Rumbling forward on heavy tracks, the tanks of the Imperial Army are capable of decimating enemy forces with overwhelming firepower. The versatile main battle tank hull is capable of being adapted to feature a wide range of alternate patterns - including devastating artillery.

This set of 79 STLS, and features the heavy 'Bombardier' tank, the long range 'Basil' tank, and the medium 'Euryale' tank, each with variants with and without bulldozer blade, and variants with holes onto which plastic open hatches from comparable plastic tank kits are compatible. There are also additional hull variants, of each tank, including an Imperial Army Bombardier tank, and hulls with extra armour, plus some kit form Bombardiers. Also included are a range of an optional details, including rear-mounted mounted dozer blade (enabling the artillery to 'dig in' prior to firing), rear mounted trailers, support struts, and shells that can be used to add features to any bases you wish to mount the tanks on.

This set has been made to be compatible with 8mm scale main line battle tanks of the Imperial Army in a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame.

Please see my other items for a free sample of this set, and a range of other 8mm scale and other wargames and hobby models. I am an enthusiastic amateur designer, self and video-tutorial taught, so am always open to constructive feedback.

Please consider liking the design and posting a make.

The All-Purpose Carrier lives up to its name as a rugged and dependable platform that has been adapted to almost every role on & off the battlefield.

This all-in-one package of M'khand-pattern All-Purpose Carrier parts allows you to build your ideal APC-based vehicle to your exact needs. Contains all previously released APC-chassis related files***, both free and paid, adapted to 1:300 scale for mass-scale wargames.

Turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern APC & Lemoine Russel turrets.

To use meshmixer builder, open with meshmixer (a free program from autodesk) and ctrl-click in the object browser the items you wish to have as one piece. Then go to File and Export. Your merged piece is ready for repair and slicing.

Alternatively, individual part stls can be assembled in 3Dbuilder or another program of your choice where they should snap together.

***Non-IFV turrets, Christie suspension sides and artillery cannons for unarmoured hulls not included***

Worried about that big hordes running towards you?? Yes, WE HAVE THE SOLUTION.

Tired of seeing the enemy aircrafts hunting your troops unchallenged?? We have the solution.
Afraid of enemy long range units shooting down your BTS?? We have the solution.
Worried about that big hordes running towards you?? Yes, WE HAVE THE SOLUTION.

Here you can find 3 wonderful "solutions": anti air tank, missile launcher tank and mortar tank (note that this one is modelled after the newest version, not the classic one).

They all share the same chasis thanks to STC magic and the same turret thanks to MkHand Industries amazing work. Simply print one chasis, one turret and a pair of mirrored weapon options for the tanks you desire, or mix and match then for fun results xD.

As always, I included both supported and unsupported versions.

This is a remix with the following parts:
Track guards: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3647995
Skull insignia: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:399182
Body, turret and weapons by MkHand Industries: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/epic-scale-anti-air-artillery

UPDATE: Added a ZIP with all files in case Thingiverse does its magic again...
Apparently clicking the download all button leads to the 404 page, simply go to thing files tab and download the zip file, simple workaround for a buggy site.

UPDATE: Test printed nicely, except for the missiles that printed kind of weird, I resupported them and reuploaded the fixed files (also updated the ZIP file).

UPDATE 15/Dec/2020: The antiair cannons were too long for my like, so I added 2 more versions closer to the 40k model proportion, so now you can choose xD (also updated the ZIP file).

UPDATE 15/01/2021: Added options with 0 and 1 missiles left (so you can have all possible configurations)

This model is designed for use in Games Workshop's 6mm scale table top wargame, Epic 40,000 (and precessors/successors). They have since abandoned all support for Epic, so I modeled this in Autodesk Inventor for any avid wargamers.

I don't believe there are any official rules for the Minotaur in Epic 40k, but I really like the look of this beast compared to the Basilisk. It adds a bit more variety, or allows the player to field a 30k-themed force.

Epic has been re-released as a titans-only game called Adeptus Titanicus. It is nominally 8mm scale instead of 6mm, so I suggest that anyone wanting to print this for AT scenery or to play 8mm Epic should upscale it by 125%.
